pageContext.claim: “For 10 years, I've been hearing about this guy, Brett Kavanaugh, I didn't know. But I've long heard he should be. But I gave it to him in the White House.”
pageContext.analysis: A decade ago Trump was not yet deeply involved in politics and so it’s doubtful that he had heard of Kavanaugh. Moreover, reports suggest that the Federalist society has guided the president’s judicial picks — including for the Supreme Court.
